89.1	War_on_Drugs	War on Drugs	The War on Drugs is a campaign of prohibition and foreign military aid and military intervention being undertaken by the United States government, with the assistance of participating countries, intended to both define and reduce the illegal drug trade. This initiative includes a set of drug policies of the United States that are intended to discourage the production, distribution, and consumption of illegal psychoactive drugs. The term "War on Drugs" was first used by President Richard Nixon in 1971.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/32/Colpolwpowell.png/220px-Colpolwpowell.png
